Consider the set of complex number $A, B, C$ and $S$ defined as
$$
\begin{aligned}
& A=\{z:|| z+2|-| z-2||=2\} \\
& B=\left\{z: \arg \left(\frac{z-1}{z}\right)=\frac{\pi}{2}\right\} \\
& C=\{z: \arg (z-1)=\pi\} \\
& S=\left\{z: \operatorname{Re}\left(\frac{z-1}{z+1}\right)=0\right\}
\end{aligned}
$$

If $z_1, z_2, z_3 \in S$, then find the minimum value of $\left|z_1+z_2\right|^2+\left|z_2+z_3\right|^2+\left|z_3+z_1\right|^2$.
